@fhowen , hmm, this seems a bug ;
the reason is that we cannot use "arg_params=mx.nd.load('lenet_2GPU-0005.params')" directly, because mx.nd.load() is not just return  arg_params but also return aux_params, so we should seperate the arg_params from the returned dict, and then feed into mx.model.FeedForward(...), can refer to https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet/blob/master/python/mxnet/model.py#L425
acturally, the mx.nd.load() interface is a bit puzzling for users, maybe @tqchen , can add seperate interface, like mx.nd.load_arg(), mx.nd.load_aus()
